3%2F08%2F15%2Fharris-county-elections-changes-ruling%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSoon%2520after%2520the%2520election%252C%252021%2Cby%2520that%2520judge%2520is%2520pending.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Texas%20Tribune%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20voting%20centers%20in%20Harris%20County%20experienced%20ballot%20shortages%20for%20short%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20voting%20machine%20issues%2C%20and%20long%20wait%20times%2C%20an%20investigation%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.houstonpublicmedia.org%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Felections%2F2023%2F04%2F24%2F449769%2Fharris-county-republican-election-judges-ballot-paper-shortage-intentional-claim-no-evidence-backing-up-surfaced%2F%5C%22%3EHouston%20Public%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20losing%20candidates%20overstated%20the%20impacts%20of%20these%20administrative%20problems%20and%20that%20there%20was%20no%20impact%20on%20election%20outcomes.%20Their%20investigation%20also%20showed%20that%20similar%20past%20issues%20had%20happened%20under%20both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20state's%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20still%20hear%20the%20county's%20challenge%20to%20the%20bill%2C%20officially%20known%20as%20SB%201750%2C%20on%20November%2028%2C%20weeks%20after%20the%202023%20elections%20are%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristian%20Menefee%2C%20attorney%20for%20Harris%20County%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.houstonpublicmedia.org%2Farticles%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Felections%2F2023%2F08%2F22%2F460232%2Ftexas-supreme-court-says-harris-county-must-abolish-its-elections-administrators-office-by-september-1%2F%5C%22%3Etold%20Houston%20Public%20Media%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20law%20is%20unconstitutional%20under%20the%20Texas%20state%20Constitution%20because%20it%20only%20affects%20a%20single%20county%2C%20but%20admitted%20that%20the%20challenge%20was%20unlikely%20to%20succeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20it%20would%20be%20wise%20to%20abolish%20the%20office%20and%20then%20later%20to%20try%20to%20recreate%20it%2C%20absent%20the%20Texas%20Supreme%20Court%20telling%20us%20that%20the%20legislators'%20law%20violates%20the%20Constitution%20and%20should%20not%20be%20rewritten%20in%20any%20way%2C%20which%20I%20would%20say%2C%20given%20their%20decision%20today%2C%20it's%20unlikely%20you're%20going%20to%20see%20the%20court%20say%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Menefee%20told%20Houston%20Public%20Media%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20court's%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Texas%20Office%20of%20the%20Attorney%20General%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHouston%20is%20electing%20a%20mayor%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20eight%20years%20as%20Turner%20reaches%20his%20term%20limit.%20There%20are%2014%20candidates%2C%20but%20polls%20show%20a%20close%20race%20between%20two%20Democrats%3A%20Congresswoman%20Sheila%20Jackson%20Lee%20and%20State%20Sen.%20John%20Whitmire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-greg-abbott-houston-mayor-race-harris-county-election-office-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693509972000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f0c4e05114270019ae6452%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-greg-abbott-houston-mayor-race-harris-county-election-office-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Texas%20Supreme%20Court%20denied%20an%20injunction%20to%20save%20the%20Harris%20County%20election%20office%2C%20which%20will%20close%20Friday%20as%20part%20of%20a%20new%20law%20championed%20by%20state%20Republican%20leaders.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22khawkinson%40insider.com%20(Katie%20Hawkinson%20)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A90%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-greg-abbott-houston-mayor-race-harris-county-election-office-2023-8%22%2C%22cdn