ee%20applies%20across%20the%20board%20to%20X's%202%2C200%20arbitration%20cases%2C%20that%20would%20amount%20to%20around%20%243.5%20million%2C%20with%20other%20fees%20possibly%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20company's%20lawyers%20have%20argued%20that%20it%20did%20not%20mandate%20its%20employees%20to%20resolve%20any%20issues%20in%20arbitration%2C%20so%20it%20should%20not%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20the%20larger%20portion%20of%20the%20filing%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Mr.%20Woodfield%20and%20others%20in%20a%20similar%20situation%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20out%20of%20arbitration%20and%20move%20their%20cases%20to%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693504860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Flesbcfj8_elon-musk-with-model-y-afp-1200_625x300_25_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musks-x-sued-by-thousands-of-employees-over-severance-pay-report-4346791%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20filing%20fees%20alone%20for%20that%20volume%20of%20cases%20could%20amount%20to%20%243.5%20million.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musks-x-sued-by-thousands-of-employees-over-severance-pay-report-4346791%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musks-x-sued-by-thousands-of-employees-over-severance-pay-report-4346791%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Felon-musks-x-sued-by-thousands-of-employees-over-severance-pay-report-4346791%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Supreme%20Court%20Questions%20Convict%20Over%20Payment%20Of%20Fine%20In%20Bilkis%20Bano%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20questioned%20one%20of%20the%20convicts%20in%20the%20Bilkis%20Bano%20gangrape%20case%20today%20about%20depositing%20the%20fine%20imposed%20on%20him%20when%20the%20hearing%20on%20the%20pleas%20challenging%20his%20remission%20was%20in%20progress.%20Appearing%20for%20convict%20Ramesh%20Rupabhai%20Chandana%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Sidharth%20Luthra%20told%20a%20bench%20of%20justices%20BV%20Nagarathna%20and%20Ujjal%20Bhuyan%20that%20the%20convicts%20have%20approached%20the%20trial%20court%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20have%20deposited%20the%20fine%20imposed%20upon%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDoes%20non-deposit%20of%20fine%20has%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20remission%3F%20Did%20you%20apprehend%20that%20non-deposit%20of%20fine%20would%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20merits%20of%20the%20case%3F%20First%20you%20ask%20for%20permission%20and%20now%20without%20permission%20you%20have%20deposited%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Luthra%20said%20non-deposition%20of%20fine%20does%20not%20affect%20the%20decision%20on%20remission%20but%20he%20had%20advised%20his%20clients%20to%20deposit%20the%20fine%20to%20%26quot%3Breduce%20the%20controversy%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccording%20to%20me%2C%20this%20has%20no%20legal%20consequence.%20But%20since%20the%20argument%20was%20raised...%20To%20reduce%20the%20controversy%2C%20we%20have%20deposited%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20petitioners%20challenging%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20convicts%2C%20has%20argued%20that%20their%20premature%20release%20is%20illegal%20as%20they%20have%20not%20served%20their%20sentence%20in%20entirety.%20It%20was%20also%20argued%20that%20since%20the%20convicts%20did%20not%20pay%20the%20fine%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2034%2C000%2C%20they%20had%20to%20undergo%20additional%20sentence%20which%20they%20have%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Luthra%20told%20the%20court%20that%20the%20convicts%20had%20filed%20an%20application%20seeking%20its%20permission%20to%20deposit%20the%20fine%2C%20as%20there%20was%20apprehension%20that%20the%20sessions%20court%20might%20not%20accept%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20filed%20certain%20applications%20with%20respect%20to%20deposit%20of%20fine.%20They%20have%20moved%20sessions%20court%20and%20it%20has%20accepted%20the%20fine%20now.%20I%20have%20advised%20them%20that%20it%20is%20appropriate%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Luthra%20said%2C%20clarifying%20there%20was%20no%20attempt%20to%20%26quot%3Boverreach%26quot%3B%20court's%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20hearing%20began%2C%20Mr%20Luthra%20defended%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20his%20client%2C%20saying%20reformation%20is%20the%20ultimate%20aim%20of%20criminal%20justice%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOtherwise%20in%20a%20murder%20case%2C%20death%20would%20be%20applied%20more%20frequently%20by%20the%20judicial%20dictat%20but%20it%20is%20applied%20in%20the%20rarest%20of%20the%20rare%20cases.%20These%20are%20not%20the%20cases%20which%20are%20beyond%20the%20remit%20of%20reformation.%20These%20are%20not%20the%20cases%20where%20there%20was%20a%20fixed%20term%20sentence.%20My%20submission%20is%20that%20arguments%20on%20society's%20cry%20for%20justice%2C%20heinous%20offence%20is%20not%20relevant%20at%20this%20stage%20as%20the%20court%20has%20not%20said%20that%20remission%20is%20not%20permissible%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20will%20resume%20on%20September%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2017%2C%20the%20top%20court%20had%20said%20that%20state%20governments%20should%20not%20be%20selective%20in%20granting%20remission%20to%20convicts%20and%20the%20opportunity%20to%20reform%20and%20reintegrate%20with%20society%20should%20be%20given%20to%20every%20prisoner%2C%20as%20the%20Gujarat%20government%20defended%20its%20decision%20of%20premature%20release%20of%20all%2011%20convicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20petition%20filed%20by%20Bilkis%20Bano%20contesting%20the%20remission%20granted%20to%20them%2C%20several%20other%20petitions%20--%20including%20one%20by%20CPM%20leader%20Subhashini%20Ali%2C%20independent%20jo